author: hwright
msg: A bit more use of the wc_db transaction mechanism.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/wc_db.c
(set_props_baton, temp_op_delete_baton):
Remove WCROOT and LOCAL_RELPATH members.
(set_props_txn, temp_op_delete_txn):
Accept WCROOT and LOCAL_RELPATH params, and use them.
(svn_wc__db_op_set_props, svn_wc__db_temp_op_delete): Use a wc_db_txn.
(set_tc_baton): Remove.
(set_tc_txn2): Remove the baton struct, and use the params instead,
including the tree_conflict as the baton.
(svn_wc__db_op_set_tree_conflict): Don't use a baton, just pass the tree
conflict directly to the wc_db_txn wrapper.

author: gtully
msg: https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3198 - Allow JAAS GuestLoginModule to fail if users specify a password
new option to GuestLoginModule, credentialsInvalidate, when true, presence of a password will cause module to fail login
allowing the next module to validate the credential. Will only guest users who don't specify a password
